Citation.sAbstract: The vapour pressures of liquid (3,5; 2,6)-dimethylpyridine with toluene mixtures were measured by a static method in the range of 263.15-353.15 K. The pure components vapour pressures data and those of the mixtures were correlated with the Antoine equation. The excess enthalpies were measured at 303.15 K, by means of an isothermal calorimeter (C80 SETARAMmodel). The molar excess Gibbs energies, calculated from the vapour-liquid equilibrium data and the molar excess enthalpies compared satisfactorily with group contribution method (DISQUAC).
Citation.sTitle: Isothermal vapour pressures and excess functions of 3,5- and 2,6-dimethylpyridine with toluene measurement and prediction
